    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="873"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d873">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.112 B61/62.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Mexican Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 15, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 81.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to the embassy’s note of the 25th of May
                    stating that the authorities of El Paso have instituted proceedings against the
                    captors of Edwin Blatt and Lawrence Converse and against Ascension Archuleta,
                    the brother of one of the captors, and requesting that this Government cause the
                    release of these persons, I have the honor to inclose herewith copies of a
                    letter of the 1st instant and inclosure from the governor of Texas,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d873fn1">Not printed.</note> from which you will observe that none
                    of the persons mentioned in your note is in prison in that State and that
                    Ascension Archuleta, who has been under arrest, has now been released as the
                    result of habeas corpus proceedings.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
